Package: rwevalidate
Title: Validate Patient Cohorts for Real-World Evidence Studies on OMOP CDM
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Hamid", "Tavakoli", email = "htavakoli@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Validates instantiated patient cohorts on an OMOP Common Data
    Model database for real-world-evidence (RWE) studies. From a single
    function call it produces a structured HTML and JSON validation report
    covering concept coverage, cohort attrition, temporal data density, and
    covariate feasibility against a comparator. The checks are aligned with
    the U.S. Food and Drug Administration guidance on real-world data and
    evidence (FDA, 2023, <https://www.fda.gov/media/171667/download>), the
    HARPER protocol template (Wang and others, 2022,
    <doi:10.1002/pds.5507>), and the RECORD-PE reporting statement (Langan
    and others, 2018, <doi:10.1136/bmj.k3532>).
